cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with classical realizability and arithmetical formul{\ae}, which are topics closely related to logic.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the specification problem and the language used in the game-theoretic approach.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper deals with the complexity of the game and the completeness of the game in different cases.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper uses interaction constants to do substitution over execution threads, which is related to data structures and algorithms.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possible category as the paper adopts a game-theoretic point of view to characterize the universal realizers of a formula.
